ecute_tasks()\n    cbo.estimate_build_time()\n\n# The task description is: Create a social networking application called CollaborateCraft with features for user profiles, project management, messaging, and code sharing/version control. Based on this task description, I have improved the solution.", "suggestion": "LOCATION: `execute_tasks` method in `CollaborativeBuildOptimizer` class\nISSUE: The `execute_tasks` method is incomplete and does not execute tasks in the correct order based on dependencies.\nSUGGESTION: Implement the `execute_tasks` method to first retrieve the task order using `get_task_order` from `TaskManager`, then execute each task in that order, marking them as complete afterward.\n\nHere is the corrected `execute_tasks` method:\n\n```python\ndef execute_tasks(self):\n    task_order = self.task_manager.get_task_order()\n    print(\"Executing tasks in the following order:\", task_order)\n    for task_id in task_order:\n        print(f\"Executing task {task_id}...\")\n        time.sleep(2)  # Simulate task execution time\n        self.task_manager.mark_task_complete(task_id)\n        print(f\"Task {task_id} completed.\")\n    self.estimate_build_time()\n```\n\nThis ensures that tasks are executed in the correct order based on their dependencies, and the build time is estimated after all tasks are completed.", "strategy": {"strategies": [{"action": "replace", "target": {"code": "def execute_tasks(self):def estimate_build_time(self):", "before_context": "    def add_task(self, task_id, code_snippet, dependencies=None):", "after_context": "    def estimate_build_time(self):"}, "new_code": "    def execute_tasks(self):\n        task_order = self.task_manager.get_task_order()\n        print(\"Executing tasks in the following order:\", task_order)\n        for task_id in task_order:\n            print(f\"Executing task {task_id}...\")\n            time.sleep(2)  # Simulate task execution time\n            self.task_manager.mark_task_complete(task_id)\n     