ue\n# Update the estimate_build_time method in CollaborativeBuildOptimizer class\n\nclass CollaborativeBuildOptimizer:\n    def estimate_build_time(self):\n        completed_tasks = [task for task, completed in self.task_manager.tasks.items() if completed]\n        num_completed_tasks = len(completed_tasks)\n        if num_completed_tasks == 0:\n            print("No tasks have been completed yet to estimate build time.")\n            return 0.0\n        else:\n            total_efficiency = sum(self.task_efficiencies[task_id] for task_id in completed_tasks)\n            average_efficiency = total_efficiency / num_completed_tasks\n\n        estimated_time = self.time_estimator.estimate_build_time(num_completed_tasks, average_efficiency)\n        print(f"Estimated build time for {num_completed_tasks} tasks: {estimated_time:.2f} seconds")\n        return estimated_time\n\n# Step 2: Analyze the existing code\n# Review solution.py for any issues or areas for improvement\n\n# Step 3: Fix existing issues\n# Identify and fix bugs or issues in the code\n\n# Step 4: Optimize the code\n# Refactor for better performance and readability\n# Implement more efficient algorithms if necessary\n\n# Step 5: Call the give_advice_and_revise action\ngive_advice_and_revise(code=solution_py, advice="Applied fix for division by zero in estimate_build_time method. Further analysis and optimization to follow.")\n```\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure that the code is robust, efficient, and adheres to best practices. Once the code is optimized, you can let Agent 2 add any missing functionality as needed.'}, 'task_results': [{'agent1': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": false, "error-msg": "Solution file already exists at C:\\\\Users\\\\70454\\\\Desktop\\\\PredictDesign\\\\results\\\\parallel_api_test\\\\runtime_configs\\\\coding\\\\task_30_workspace\\\\solution.py. Operation aborted."}'}, {'agent2': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success